HMD Global will launch the Nokia 8 Sirocco, Nokia 7 Plus, and the second-generation Nokia 6 in South Africa from April. The devices will be on sale through Cell C, MTN, Vodacom, and selected retailers. The devices were unveiled at Mobile World Congress in February, and HMD Global said it would expand its product portfolio to respond to customer requests and feedback. Its “pure, secure, and always up-to-date” Android promise has also received an endorsement from Google, with the new Nokia devices in the Android One programme. Local availability is as follows:  